  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STAR Call 1- &#x201C;Educating the Public on Voting on Policy Issues: Reducing Vote Buying in Election 2016</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Campaigns in elections in a democracy are supposed to present peaceful and open discourse of persuasion. Ideally, candidates are supposed to present reasoned arguments as to why they should be voted into office (Bratton, 2008:1). This gives voters the opportunity to sift through the messages from contestants to inform their choice of candidates and parties. However, in Africa, the desire to capture state power and the accompanying state resources has become the end game in political competition. The Ghanaian media is replete with claims of political parties and candidates in intra and inter-party contests that their opponents had gained electoral advantage over them only by offering material and financial rewards to voters. An addendum to the project is the annual democracy and governance lecture event dubbed &apos;The Kronti ne Akwamu Lecture. The topic for this year is &#x201C;Credible and Peaceful Elections: A Prerequisite for Africa&#x2019;s Progress&#x201D; and the main speaker is His Excellency Kofi Annan, former UN Secretary General. The lecture features scholars and/or practitioners of exceptional international and local repute whose interests and work focus on the promotion of democracy, good governance and inclusive development.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at achieving 4 basic related results: 1. The public/electorate is well sensitized and their choices of candidates are informed by policy issues; 2. Facts in the allegation of vote buying is ascertained at the end of the project through evidence and
reports from the field; 3. Have documented evidence in cases of allegations of vote buying in terms of modes/forms/types, and when as well as where they occur; and 4. Policy makers and law enforcement agencies use the project report to deal with the problem and influence reforms in the electoral process, especially political campaigns.</narrative>
  </description>
